<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">For the facts on the abortion issue, the <a href="http://www.guttmacher.org" target="_blank">Guttmacher Institute</a> Web site is an excellent resource for statistics and basic information.<p>
<i>Socialist Worker</i> columnist Sharon Smith has covered the right's attack on reproductive choice for the <i><a href="http://www.isreview.org" target="_blank">International Socialist Review</a></i>--see, for example, <a href="http://www.isreview.org/issues/43/abortion.shtml" target="_blank">"Abortion Rights Under Attack."</a><p>
Smith's <i><a href="http://www.haymarketbooks.org/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=PROD&amp;Store_Code=Haymarket&amp;Product_Code=WRWS" target="_blank">Women and Socialism</a></i>, published by Haymarket Books, has several essays relevant to this issue. Also see Leslie Reagan's <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FWhen-Abortion-Was-Crime-1867-1973%2Fdp%2F0520216571%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1177465378%26sr%3D8-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">When Abortion Was a Crime</a> </i>for an important look at the consequences of restrictions on the right to choose.
